---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SEO from '../components/SEO.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import DisclaimerBanner from '../components/DisclaimerBanner.astro';
---

<Layout title="Parent Choice & Disclaimers | Rabbia Ashraf & Associates">
  <SEO
    title="Parent Choice & Platform Disclaimers"
    description="Important information regarding provider selection, platform responsibilities, and service boundaries."
  />

  <DisclaimerBanner />
  <Header />

  <main class="py-12 md:py-20 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-4xl">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-8">Parent Choice & Disclaimers</h1>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100 p-8 space-y-8">

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Parent-Choice Model</h2>
          <div class="prose max-w-none text-gray-700">
            <p>Our platform operates on a parent-choice model. We believe parents are best positioned to determine which professional fits their family's needs, budget, and communication style.</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 mt-4">
              <li>Parents choose the provider they want to book.</li>
              <li>The platform gives provider information, education, and booking pathways.</li>
              <li>The platform does not assign or force a provider.</li>
              <li>Provider matching, if requested, is informational only.</li>
              <li>The platform does not guarantee that any provider is suitable for every case.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Provider Responsibility</h2>
          <div class="prose max-w-none text-gray-700">
            <p>
              Providers are independent professionals or collaborators responsible for the accuracy of their credentials, the services they offer, and compliance with applicable professional, ethical, and regional requirements.
            </p>
            <p>
              Each provider is responsible for working within their own professional scope, qualifications, license, registration, and regional legal requirements. Regulated therapy, diagnosis, assessment, or treatment is only available when the provider is legally allowed to provide it in the client's location.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Platform Responsibility</h2>
          <div class="prose max-w-none text-gray-700">
            <p>
              The platform presents provider information, education, resources, and booking pathways for parent convenience. It does not replace local medical, psychological, educational, legal, or emergency services.
            </p>
            <p>
              This platform does not guarantee diagnosis, treatment outcome, school placement, insurance coverage, or emergency support.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Emergency Disclaimer</h2>
          <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-6 text-red-800">
            <p class="font-bold mb-2">Not for Emergencies</p>
            <p>
              This platform is not suitable for emergencies, self-harm risk, abuse crisis, medical emergencies, or immediate safety concerns. In urgent situations, contact local emergency services, the nearest hospital, or a local licensed mental health professional.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
